# Role and Responsibilities

## Position

**Powertrain Lead & Main Driver**

## Overview

As the Powertrain Lead, I was responsible for overseeing the development and integration of the vehicle's powertrain subsystem throughout the Formula Bharat 2026 project. My role involved engineering calculations, subsystem planning, manufacturing support, and coordination with other vehicle subsystems to ensure successful integration.

In addition to my engineering responsibilities, I also served as the team's Main Driver, participating in vehicle testing and providing performance feedback to support design improvements.

---

## Responsibilities

### Powertrain Lead

- Planned and coordinated the powertrain subsystem development.
- Performed engineering calculations required for subsystem design.
- Assisted in component selection and design validation.
- Supported manufacturing and assembly activities.
- Worked on subsystem integration within the vehicle.
- Collaborated with other subsystem leads during vehicle development.
- Assisted in troubleshooting during assembly and testing.

### Main Driver

- Conducted vehicle testing sessions.
- Evaluated vehicle handling and drivability.
- Communicated technical feedback to the engineering team.
- Assisted in validating subsystem performance.
- Supported iterative improvements during testing.

---

## Skills Applied

- Engineering Calculations
- Mechanical Design
- Manufacturing
- System Integration
- Team Coordination
- Problem Solving
- Technical Communication
- Leadership
